			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The Famicom Titler and Famicom TV have the same 2C03 PPU as the PlayChoice. <a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_palettes#2C03_and_2C05" class="postlink">The 2C03 palette is known</a>, and it differs in several ways from what you get when you run the NES output through any reasonable NTSC decoder.<br /><br />I'm still interested in what would happen if you assume that a Super NES should be able to produce the same color as an NES through the same monitor. Anybody with a scope, an NES flash cart, and Super NES flash cart should be able to find the RGB values out of the S-PPU that produce the same center level, RMS amplitude, and phase as each NES PPU color.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

